### Phase 2: CSS basics
# CSS has this structure:
selector {
  property: value;
}

# Example:
h1 {
  color: blue;
} -> Ikkada this means: select all h1 elements and make them blue

### Three ways to add CSS
1. Inline CSS
<h1 style="color: red;">Hello</h1>   [Do not use this much bcz it becomes messy]

2. Internal CSS
<style>
  h1 {
    color: red;
  }
</style> -> Okay for practice anthee

3. External CSS
Best industry approach antaam
## HTML file:
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

## CSS file:
h1 {
  color: red;
} -> This is what you should use

Saree oka example chudhama: Styled login page
Create two files: index.html, style.css
# index.html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Login Page</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="login-card">
      <h1>Welcome Back</h1>
      <p>Please login to continue</p>

      <form>
        <label>Email</label>
        <input type="email" placeholder="Enter your email">

        <label>Password</label>
        <input type="password" placeholder="Enter your password">

        <button type="submit">Login</button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>

# styple.css
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  background-color: #f3f4f6;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 100vh;
  margin: 0;
}

.login-card {
  background-color: white;
  width: 350px;
  padding: 30px;
  border-radius: 12px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

h1 {
  margin-bottom: 5px;
}

p {
  color: #666;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}

label {
  display: block;
  margin-top: 15px;
  font-weight: bold;
}

input {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 12px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

button {
  width: 100%;
  margin-top: 20px;
  padding: 12px;
  background-color: #006241;
  color: white;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 8px;
  font-size: 16px;
  cursor: pointer;
}

button:hover {
  background-color: #004c32;
}

